data.name: Garlic Mashed Potato Casserole
data.quickTastyDescription: A creamy and flavorful mashed potato casserole with a hint of garlic, perfect for any meal!
detailedCookingInstructions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the mashed potatoes, minced garlic, sour cream, half of the shredded cheddar cheese, melted butter, salt, and black pepper.
Mix well until all ingredients are combined and creamy. You can use a hand mixer for a smoother texture if desired.
Transfer the potato mixture into a greased casserole dish and spread evenly.
Top with the remaining cheddar cheese.
Bake in the preheated oven for about 30 minutes, or until the cheese is bubbly and golden brown.
Remove from the oven and let it cool for a few minutes. Garnish with chopped chives before serving.
